The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 04 December is 9,415 (1,089.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 29 November, there were 499 new confirmed cases (57.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 November, there were 801 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 38% (302 fewer cases).
